                                                                        <font color="#0000ff">municipality </font>
                                                                    </u></strong></a>
                                                            <font color="#000000">in the Loreto area of the Upper Amazon
                                                                Basin of Peru. The community, as part of the initial stages
                                                                of the programme, are now able to manage the planting and
                                                                management of the trees.</font>
                                                        </span>
                                                        <p><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">Working
                                                                with the top authorities on rain forest studies such as the
                                                            </span><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">Institute</span><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">
                                                                of </span><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">Investigation</span><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">
                                                                of the Peruvian Rainforest in </span><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">South
                                                                America</span><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">
                                                                we have taken the following approach: if you want to look
                                                                after the forest you must first look after the people
                                                                responsible for it – the locals.</span></p>
                                                        <p><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">Our
                                                                programme is not a hand out. Simply giving does not work as
                                                                it is not a long term solution.</span></p>
                                                        <p style="line-height: 150%" class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">We
                                                                have developed a system to both provide the locals with
                                                                their immediate needs and also<span> </span>lay the
                                                                foundations of long term sustainable economies. In the
                                                                process, these local communities will reforest and maintain
                                                                vast areas of the Peruvian Amazon</span>.</p>
                                                        <p style="line-height: 150%" class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">We
                                                                use that money as an incentive. If you plant a tree, you
                                                                receive payment. This ensures that the local community is
                                                                involved immediately.</span></p>
                                                        <p style="line-height: 150%" class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'"><img
                                                                    src="frontend/images/stories/tiuk/green/plant2.JPG"
                                                                    width="136" height="242" style="float: left;" hspace="6"
                                                                    alt="The first saplings to be planted"
                                                                    title="The first saplings to be planted"
                                                                    border="0"></span></p>
                                                        <p style="line-height: 150%" class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">Each
                                                                tree needs to be maintained, so every month the tree is
                                                                checked and a maintenance fee is paid to the original
                                                                planter. This gives a residual income and ongoing
                                                                responsibility.</span></p>
                                                        <p style="line-height: 150%" class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">If
                                                                the village as a whole meets its target it receives a bonus
                                                                which can be used towards a small project.</span></p>
                                                        <p style="line-height: 150%" class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">For
                                                                every £1 paid, a small percentage is put aside as a sort of
                                                                trust fund or tax.<span>&nbsp;</span>As the trust fund
                                                                grows, a number of potential industry projects e.g., setting
                                                                up a fish farm, a small coffee plantation etc. will be
                                                                assessed and implemented by the locals.</span> </p>
                                                        <p style="line-height: 150%" class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">By
                                                                the third year newly planted trees that have been properly
                                                                maintained will also be bearing fruits which can be used for
                                                                food and sold.</span></p>
                                                        <p style="line-height: 150%" class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">These
                                                                incentives have proved very successful in combating
                                                                deforestation, encouraging reforestation, putting a stop to
                                                                hunger and poverty, getting everyone in the community
                                                                involved and dramatically improved levels of
                                                                understanding.</span></p>
